Database: structured data storage
SQL- structured Query Language (pronunced as Siquel)
PostgreSQL RDBM (reletional database management system)
pgAdmin - GUI (graphical  interface) to work with PostgreSQL

relational DB: ogranaithed as table
the table have relationship (parent tables and child tables)


Terminology for a table in Database
How the data on a relational db?

- TABLE
fields: the 1 row of the table which holds the headings of each column
a record or a row: horizontal :individual entry on a table
column: vertical data associated with specific field

NULL  value: это отсутствие значения а не 0

DATATYPES on DB:
-varchar : short string
-text: text field
-integers
-smallint
-date time
-boolian


CONSTRAINTS   - its a condition  ( чтобы данные например были одного типа)

- not null: has to be valid data ( no absence)
- DEFAULT (по умалчанию) sets of default data
- UNIQUE: DONT ACCEPT REPEATED DATA
- PRINARY KEY: not null + unique . usualy is used to create a serial number that indetifies the row


